From: Ghaf contributors <ghaf@tii.ae>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: honor RM connect state over DP-lib HPD on dual-mode connectors

On the AGX Orin the DisplayPort connector is DP++ dual-mode: displayId 0x100
(SOR_DP_A) and 0x200 (SINGLE_TMDS_A) are the same physical DP_EXT connector,
DDC partners sharing one DRM connector with two encoders.

A passive HDMI adapter presents a TMDS sink but still asserts HPD, so the DP
library reports the DP displayId connected. DRM detect stops at that first
connected encoder, never probing the TMDS partner; EDID reads then go to the
DP displayId over AUX where no sink answers (NV_ERR_GENERIC), leaving no EDID
and no modes.

RM DDC/LOAD detection (GET_CONNECT_STATE) gets this right. Trust it: if RM
says the DP displayId is not connected, don't let the DP-lib HPD guess override
that, so detection falls through to the partner. A real DP sink reports
connected on both, so native DP is unaffected.
---
diff --git a/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-dpy.c b/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-dpy.c
index c94a9cd..0aec8e3 100644
--- a/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-dpy.c
+++ b/nvdisplay/src/nvidia-modeset/src/nvkms-dpy.c
@@ -2873,6 +2873,21 @@ NvBool nvDpyGetDynamicData(
     } else if (nvConnectorUsesDPLib(pConnectorEvo)) {
         connectedList = nvDPLibDpyIsConnected(pDpyEvo) ?
             oneDpyIdList : nvEmptyDpyIdList();
+        /*
+         * DP++ dual-mode: on a dual-mode DisplayPort connector a passive
+         * HDMI adapter asserts HPD but presents no DP sink, so the DP
+         * library -- which only sees HPD -- reports the DP displayId as
+         * connected, and its AUX probes then fail forever. RM's DDC/LOAD
+         * detection can tell the difference and reports the sink on the
+         * TMDS DDC-partner displayId instead. If RM says this displayId is
+         * not connected, believe RM, so detection falls through to the
+         * partner. A real DP sink is reported connected by both, so the
+         * native DP path is unaffected.
+         */
+        if (!nvDpyIdListIsEmpty(connectedList) &&
+            nvDpyIdListIsEmpty(nvRmGetConnectedDpys(pDispEvo, oneDpyIdList))) {
+            connectedList = nvEmptyDpyIdList();
+        }
     } else if (nvConnectorIsDPSerializer(pConnectorEvo)) {
         if (pConnectorEvo->dpSerializerCaps.supportsMST &&
             !nvDpyEvoIsDPMST(pDpyEvo)) {
